OL,5, A man plans to sue a nursing home      
OL,6, because, he says, during the pandemic  
OL,7, his mother was put on end-of-life care 
OL,8, without her family being told.         
OL,10,FAntonia Stowell, 87, did not have the  
OL,11,Fmental capacity to consent because she 
OL,12,Fhad dementia, say the family's lawyers.
OL,14,FHer son, Tony Stowell, said if         
OL,15,Fend-of-life care had been discussed, he
OL,16,Fwould not have agreed to it.           
OL,18,FRose Villa nursing home in Hull says   
OL,19,Fall proper process in Mrs Stowell's    
OL,20,Fcare was followed with precision.      
